13/02/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- A court in Thessaloniki sentenced two Bulgarian nationals to life in prison Thursday (12 February) for attempting to bring 4,500 ecstasy pills into the country. Georgi Konstantinov, 41, and Alexander Vassilev, a 31-year-old police special operations officer, were found guilty of smuggling the drugs from Germany.
Also Thursday, police raided a greenhouse in Thessaloniki and uncovered 22 kg of heroin, allegedly smuggled into Greece from Albania. Two Albanian brothers were arrested. (AFP - 12/02/04)
